# /business-case: Five Case Model Business Case

Walks through the Five Case Model: Strategic (why do it), Economic (value for money), Commercial (deliverability), Financial (affordability), and Management (plan to deliver). Produces one structured business case document. Delegates Economic Case computation to `/cost-benefit` so numbers are consistent with a fresh CBA run.

```
/longlist          = "Brainstorm benefits and costs"
     ↓
/cost-benefit      = "Monetise and compute NPV"
     ↓
/business-case     = "Wrap in the Five Case Model for a spending bid"  (this skill)
```

Default output: one complete Five Case business case at the requested stage and proportionality. Power users can generate only one case via `--section strategic` or similar.

## Arguments

```
/business-case [project description] [options]
```

**Examples:**
```
/business-case "New hospital wing in Greater Manchester"
/business-case --stage obc --framework uk-gb
/business-case --framework au-vic --stage fbc
/business-case --from longlist-schools-2026-04-10.md
/business-case --section strategic,economic
/business-case --with-cba cba-schools-2026-04-10.md
```

**Options:**
- `--framework <name>` : `uk-gb` (default), `eu-brg`, `wb`, `adb`, or `au-vic`. Auto-detected from context if not set.
- `--stage <name>` : `soc` (Strategic Outline Case, high-level), `obc` (Outline Business Case, default, full detail on shortlisted options), or `fbc` (Full Business Case, final negotiated version).
- `--proportionality <level>` : Override auto-detected depth. `light` (under GBP 1m), `standard` (GBP 1-10m, default), `detailed` (GBP 10-100m), `comprehensive` (over GBP 100m).
- `--section <name>` : Emit only one sub-component. Options: `full` (default, all 5 cases), `strategic`, `economic`, `commercial`, `financial`, `management`, `exec` (executive summary only). Combinable with commas.
- `--from <file.md>` : Import project, options, costs, benefits, and Cash flow tags from a `/longlist` markdown file.
- `--with-cba <file.md>` : Import an existing `/cost-benefit` output as the Economic Case. Skips the CBA computation.
- `--format <type>` : `markdown` (default, always generated), `xlsx`, `word`, `pptx`, `pdf`, or `all`. Comma-separate for multiple.
- `--client "Name"` : Add "Prepared for" metadata.

## Stage and proportionality

| Flag | Stage | Depth | Cost threshold |
|------|-------|-------|----------------|
| `soc` | Strategic Outline Case | Wide option list, rough costs, qualitative benefits | Typically under GBP 10m |
| `obc` | Outline Business Case (default) | Shortlisted options with full CBA, benefits register, procurement strategy, governance | GBP 10-100m |
| `fbc` | Full Business Case | Single preferred option, confirmed numbers, contracts, management plan | Over GBP 50m |

Proportionality drives depth. A GBP 500k programme should have a 5-page business case; a GBP 500m infrastructure project should have a 50-page one. Auto-detected from the total cost if not overridden.

